                    </div>
                    <span>Not just a "How do I..." book, but also a "Why should I..." book.  <p>Richter writes in an easy, conversational, and readable style about difficult and technical topics related to Win32 programming - thread management and local storage, differences in the handing of DLLs in Win32 and Win16, using virtual memory, etc.   In addition, the author makes explicit distinctions between the behavior of 95 and NT when appropriate.<p>Highly recommended.</span>
                  
