                    <span>Jeffrey Richter's Advanced Windows is easily the most frequently used (and  borrowed) book on my computer bookshelf.  It is well written, complete, and  contains descriptions and examples of non-GUI Windows programming you  simply can not find anywhere else.  I plan on buying both of his new books  as well.  All of his books are utterly without hype - it's like reading  just the meaty parts of MSJ/MSDN magazine.  Long Live Jeff Richter!</span>
                  
              
